### Adjust margin and stroke for Recharts LineChart components (TypeScript/JSX)

Source: https://github.com/recharts/recharts/blob/main/storybook/stories/GettingStarted.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to customize the appearance and layout of a Recharts line chart by adjusting component properties. It increases the chart's margin to accommodate labels and sets a dashed stroke style for the `CartesianGrid` for improved visual clarity. This allows for fine-tuning the chart's presentation.

```tsx
import { LineChart, Line, CartesianGrid, XAxis, YAxis } from 'recharts';
const renderLineChart = (
  <LineChart width={600} height={300} data={data} margin={{ top: 5, right: 20, bottom: 5, left: 0 }}>
    <Line type="monotone" dataKey="uv" stroke="#8884d8" />
    <CartesianGrid stroke="#ccc" strokeDasharray="5 5" />
    <XAxis dataKey="name" />
    <YAxis />
  </LineChart>
);
```

